entry.def: If you say that a change or an event is overdue, you mean that you think it should have happened before now.

example.ex: I'll go home and pay an overdue visit to my mother.
example.tran: 我将回家看望母亲，其实我早该回去了。

entry.def: Overdue sums of money have not been paid, even though it is later than the date on which they should have been paid.

example.ex: Teachers have joined a strike aimed at forcing the government to pay overdue salaries and allowances.
example.tran: 教师加入了旨在迫使政府支付拖欠薪水和津贴的罢工。

entry.def: An overdue library book has not been returned to the library, even though the date on which it should have been returned has passed.
